I&#39;m not sure what&#39;s best for your situation, but I suspect the problem 
is that there&#39;s no one artifact &#39;heritrix&#39; with a single JAR 
deliverable. Rather, the artifact &#39;heritrix&#39; creates the 
&#39;.tar.gz&#39;/&#39;.zip&#39; expandable distributions for running Heritrix standalone.

It depends on three subprojects that each *do* deliver a JAR: 
&#39;heritrix-commons&#39;, &#39;heritrix-modules&#39;, and &#39;heritrix-engine&#39;. (Each of 
these is a prerequisite for the next in turn, with &#39;heritrix-commons&#39; 
being foundational classes that may be of use outside the crawler; 
&#39;heritrix-modules&#39; being more-specific functionality mostly for the 
crawler but perhaps sometimes usable elsewhere; and &#39;heritrix-engine&#39; 
being the main() class and web console for configuring/managing crawls.)

If you include each of those, I think you&#39;ll have all the H3 classes 
available for your project.

Hope this helps,

- Gordon @ IA

